<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>believe in something • believe something</xh5><p> <i>believe in something—</i>1. have trust in smth.; feel sure of the value of smth.: The United States <u>believes in</u> the great potential of Africa. 2. feel sure of the existence of smth.: Clever farmers made good use of the belief of these people who <u>believed in</u> ghosts.</p><p> <i>believe something—</i>feel sure of the truth of smth.: I want to <u>believe</u> this story, but then again I still have a lot of doubts about its authenticity.</p> </entry>
